node.text:
The landscapes of Acadia provide a pretty amazing backdrop for exploring a little photography...

but really, for a lot of things. For a little relaxation, fresh air, visiting with my parents (and their Mainecoon), hiking, eating lots of lobster, and just plain taking a few days off. Like all the best things in life, it’s never long enough. 

1. Jordan Pond
2. From Gorham Mountain
3. From Northeast Harbor
4. Thuya boat landing with Captain Marcus, a.k.a. Dad
5. Otter Cliffs
6. Bernard, ME
7. My parents in Bernard
8. Hangin with Murphy- tryin to get some love
9. With my mother
10. From Pemetic Mountain trail

People photos by @evanlaettner
Selfies and Landscape pics by yours truly

#maine #mainecoon #acadianationalpark 
#landscapephotography #family

node.text:
Turner update:
She is fully recovered from her surgery three weeks ago to remove a cancerous tumor from her jaw. Back to running in the yard, chilling in the studio, chasing cats, and being her sweet self! We’re hoping that it doesn’t come back and enjoying all the moments we have together. She does seem a bit more affectionate in recent days. And she now has this badass snaggle tooth look. Thank you so much for all the well wishes and positive vibes ❤️ 

#mygirl #twoturners #happytogether #dogsofinsta #oldgirl #snaggletooth

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ashley Harwood in Port Townsend, Washington with @ashleyharwoodturning. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text: About to start the last day of class here at @ptwoodschool - and excited to share what my students have been working on! It’s incredibly gratifying as a teacher to see the look on someone’s face when they take something off of the lathe that they would not have believed they could make 😊 That never gets old. #neverstoplearning #woodturning #teacherlife
